Pre-Game Insights: Estonia have indulged in four friendly fixtures during the 2024 international calendar to date, including a penalty-shootout success over Lithuania on June 11.
Slovakia are still reeling from Euro 2024 heartbreak, falling short of the top-two places in their qualifying group.

Thursday night will see Slovakia return to competitive action for the first time since that fateful day in Gelsenkirchen on June 30, when the Eastern Europeans looked set to knock tournament favourites England out of Euro 2024 at the round-of-16 stage.
